Washington Capitals (3-0-2, fourth in the Metropolitan) vs. Ottawa Senators (2-3-0, seventh in the Atlantic)
Ottawa, Ontario; Monday, 7 p.m. EDT
FANDUEL SPORTSBOOK
 LINE: Senators +140, Capitals -171; over/under is 6
BOTTOM LINE: The Ottawa Senators host the Washington Capitals.
Ottawa went 23-28-5 overall during the 2020-21 season while going 14-10-4 at home. The Senators averaged 3.8 penalties and 9.1 penalty minutes per game.
Washington finished 36-15-5 overall with a 19-7-2 record on the road during the 2020-21 season. The Capitals recorded 314 assists on 188 total goals last season.
The matchup Monday is the first meeting this season for the two teams.
INJURIES: Senators: Matt Murray: day to day (head), Shane Pinto: out (upper body).
Capitals: None listed.
